args:
Hey, folks! Chitose here, ready to inspire!
Pre-heat those ovens to 375 degrees,
because here comes a bona fide cutie pie!
Everybody feeling good today?
Chitose! You're SO cute! Gimme a smile!
No pushing, now! There's more than\nenough of me to go around!
All right! Time to ride this cheer wave\nand make cuteness diplomacy a success!

Yup. And I'm appointing you as the official
ambassador. You'll be using the Halidom
as your home base, per my arrangement
with {player_name}.
Mouse Wyrmclan Leader and Chitose's Master\nMitsuhide
We're swiftly approaching an era where\nwe'll need Alberian connections beyond\nwhat we've established in the Halidom.

If you'll recall Hinomoto's One Hundred
Poems by One Hundred People:
＂Good relations make for peaceful times.＂
We should get a head start on that.

So get out there and weaponize that
cuteness for international diplomacy!
We'll call it...cuteness diplomacy.
Good luck!
Maaan, I was super-duper worried about\nhow this would go, but I'm killin' it!\nCuteness is universal!
And now, I'm gonna go all-out with the\ndiplomacy today! ...Wait, what's going\non over there?
Some kind of trouble? Hey, no better way\nto make friends than to lend a helping\nhand! Aaand we're off to the races!
...I'm telling you, I'm not really up for it.\nThat sort of thing isn't in my wheelhouse.
But you shop all the time, don't you?\nCan't you help me? Pleeease?
I only shop when I need groceries...\nand I'm not even a chef to begin with!
Do me a favor and drop it, okay?\nThere's a good girl.
Person in need: discovered! Wait, Vice?\nWhat the heck's going on here?
That you, Chitose? Hey. I guess this kid\nwants to buy a gift for her sick mother.
That's right, but the flower I want to get\nher is sooo expensive. I don't have enough\nwith just my allowance.
So she's asking me to go instead and\nhaggle the price down for her. Can't see\nit working, no matter how you slice it.
Ooh, I see! Yeah, that's probably totally\nbeyond you, Vice.
You're a bit of a soft touch, and not much\nfor driving a hard bargain. But fear not,\nlittle one, for I am here!
My irresistible charm will see\nyour wish granted lickety-split!
Uh, mind explaining how ＂charm＂ is\ngonna get a merchant to cut their profits?
Hee hee! Watch and learn.\nTo the market, sidekicks!
Um, excuse me! Do you still have that\nflower I asked about earlier?
I do indeed. Did you bring enough\nmoney this time?
All right! Watch a master in action!\nHey there, mister. I'm gonna be taking\npoint for the nervous little lady here.
So this is the famous flower, huh?\nWoooow, it really leaves an impression!\nWhat'll it run us?
That there's an exceptionally rare breed\nof flower. It's 15,000 rupies in all.
Bwuh-what?! I could buy the whole veggie\nsection at the grocery store for that much!
Do you have any idea how hard it was to\nget my hands on? I'm already giving you\na bargain at 15,000.
Reeeally? Like, REALLY really? You\ncouldn't throw us a teensy-weensy bone?
Picture this: If I adorned myself with this\nlovely flower, I could be even CUTER than\nI am now.
Do the math, my friend. Cute plus cute\nequals even cuter. Don't you want to\nexperience the ultimate in adorableness?

Then let's make a deal! All I need is one
measly flower to usher in a cutesplosion
unlike anything the world's ever seen!
The power to make it happen lies with you!
Now's your chance to prove yourself an ally\nof cuteness! Won't you please knock a little\noff the price of that flower? P-L-E-A-S-E?
Well, I'd hate to deprive the world of a\nnew age of cuteness... How does 10,000\nsound?
Oooh, I think you can do a little better!\nLet's say...7,000. Perfect, right? Mwah!
The cuteness compels me...!\nFine, 7,000 it is!
Sold! Now, I'll adorn myself with it,\nlike so...and voila! Grab your bib and\nhave a slice of THIS cutie pie!
Hee hee... Oh, cuteness, I worship thee...
Ta-daaa! Here's your flower, little lady.
Keep it. Knowing how sweet you are and\nhow much you love your mom is payment\nenough.
Really? You're so amazing, Chitose!\nYou're the total package!
The way you won over that merchant\nwith your cuteness was like magic!
It wasn't magic. It was just negotiation...
Sure, it wasn't MAGIC, per se, but there IS\na little secret behind my appeal, y'know!
Then pull up a chair for storytime, friends.\nI call this one: ＂The Secret Tale of Chitose\nthe Cute!＂ You listen carefully too, Vice!
No bellyaching about it, kitchen jockey!\nEars open! Now... Long ago, in a land far,\nfar away...
